cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.SE, cs.LG

The paper deals with process calculi and their extensions, which are typically studied in the areas of logic (LO), programming languages (PL), formal languages and automata theory (FL), software engineering (SE), and machine learning (LG). The paper specifically focuses on the psi-calculi framework, which is a family of applied process calculi, and extends it to include action priorities. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
